class ShoppingCart {
    public int itemCount;
    public double totalPrice;

    public ShoppingCart() {
        itemCount = 0;
        totalPrice = 0.0;
    }

    public void addItem(double price) {
        itemCount++;
        totalPrice += price;
    }

    public void applyDiscount(double discountPercent) {
        totalPrice -= totalPrice * (discountPercent / 100);
    }

    public void removeItem(double price) {
        if (itemCount > 0 && totalPrice >= price) {
            itemCount--;
            totalPrice -= price;
        }
    }
}",

Assuming an addItem method has been invoked, can observing an increase in itemCount help infer that the totalPrice will be greater than it was before invoking addItem?
